2026-06-23 22:48:13,584 DEBUG msg #12: UserMessage tool_result(toolu_016ZEJmcaX9JkuMRUwaaWVz3): {"assignees":[{"id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwOTUyOTQ4","login":"SilvioBaratto","name":"Silvio Angelo Baratto Roldan","databaseId":0}],"body":"## Goal\nEncode the official WC2026 Round-of-32 bracket template and the best-third-place selection/assignment rules as pure data + functions, so a later-cycle simulator can deterministically resolve `LAST_32` from final group standings. This is **data and pure rules only — no simulation, no probabilities, no network.**\n\n## Context\nWC2026 has **48 teams → 12 groups**; the top 2 of each group **plus the 8 best third-placed teams** advance to the Round of 32. The football-data.org API returns knockout slot teams as `null` until the groups resolve, so the bracket must be derived, not fetched.\n\nTwo pieces of canonical FIFA data are required:\n1. The **R32 template** — which group-winner (`1A`…`1L`), runner-up (`2A`…`2L`), and best-third placeholder (`3X`) meet in each of the 16 ties.\n2. The **best-third-place assignment table** — a lookup keyed by *which* 8 of the 12 third-placed groups qualified, mapping each third-place placeholder slot to a concrete group. (Same mechanism as the historical 24-team Euro/World Cup third-place tables, expanded for 12 groups / 8 qualifying thirds.)\n\nConsume the `GroupStanding` value object defined in the live adapter (issue #3) as the input type for the resolver. Team names arriving in standings are already canonical via the crosswalk (issue #1), so the resolved pairs need no further normalization. Keep this module a one-way consumer of the `GroupStanding` **type** only — `live.py` must never import this module (avoid cycles).\n\nConventions: module `\"\"\"docstring\"\"\"` → `from __future__ import annotations` → `logger`; pure functions < 10 lines; frozen module-level data structures. FIFA group-stage tiebreak order for ranking thirds: points, then goal difference, then goals for, then further criteria.\n\n